6.60	The_Black_Watch_(Royal_Highland_Regiment)_of_Canada	The Black Watch (Royal Highland Regiment) of Canada	The Black Watch (Royal Highland Regiment) of Canada is a reserve infantry regiment in 34 Brigade Group, Land Force Quebec Area. The regiment is located on rue de Bleury in Montreal, Quebec, Canada, and is currently commanded by Lieutenant Colonel Bruno Plourde. The regiment's armoury was designated a National Historic Site of Canada in 2008.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f9/Blackwatch_72.jpg
